{
  "stem": "15962.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But he was able to save him from certain death in that first transport that went to the gas chamber on March 7, by hiding him in the hospital compound.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He was actually, somehow, hidden in the rafters.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So that was his first escape.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He also managed, somehow, either to bribe Mengele or get him into that group of 89 children, even though he would not have normally passed muster, because he was so small.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So then, he did the death-- they did the death march together.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they ended up in the same carriage that we were.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And while the carriage was waiting in Moravska Ostrava-- that was the first [INAUDIBLE] in-- in the Czech Republic, they jumped out and were able to-- because they were from that town.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were able to reach the house of a friend.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But they knew that this was a house with two apartments-- that one of the bells was their friend's and the other bell was a Nazi sympathizer.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were faced with the choice of life and death.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were lucky and pushed the right button.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were hidden for the rest of the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And his name is Dorf Kulcher And he is a professor at-- in Jerusalem.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And his father just died.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "His father was one of the main authors of some of the books [BACKROUND NOISE] describing Auschwitz after the war and devoted his life to the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But his mother, the wife of this person, was shipped to Stutthof with my mother.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they both died there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And only two years ago, they went to this camp and were able to find the card catalogue that the Germans kept there.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
